						<summary>

						<p>This is damaged and is dated <hi rend="bold">Śaka 1262,</hi> the other details being lost. It registers the excavation of a tank called <hi rend="bold">Haṁpeya-Doṇe</hi> in <hi rend="bold">Kundurupe</hi> by <hi rend="bold">Chikka Bommayya-Nāyaka,</hi> son of <hi rend="bold">Gaṅgeya-Nāyaka</hi> of <hi rend="bold">Holakal,</hi> in the reign of the Hoysaḷa king <hi rend="bold">Vīra-Ballāḷa (III),</hi> son of <hi rend="bold">Vīra-Narasiṅga,</hi> ruling from <hi rend="bold">Dōrasamudra.</hi> Bommaya-Nāyaka is stated to have been governing <hi rend="bold">Nidugalla-rājya.</hi></p>						

						</summary>
